Git Commands

1. To get the status of untracked files or newly added file we use 
    Git status
2. To add the untracked files to the staging area we use
    Git add <filename> or Git add . (. indicates all files)
3.To commit to local repo we use
    git commit -m "message"
4. To push to remote repo we use
    git push origin <branchname> 
        ex: git push origin main (main:main is the branch name)
5. To get the history of previous commits we use 
    git log
6.To list the branches we use
    git branch -a
7. To checkout to the branch we use
        git checkout <branchname>
8. To create a new Branch in local we use
    git branch <branch name>
9. To push local branch to remote we use
    git push origin <branch name>
10. To reset or to remove a file from staging area
    git reset <filename>


